# UI Component Guidelines

## shadcn/ui Integration
This project uses shadcn/ui components located in [src/components/ui/](mdc:src/components/ui/).

## Available Components
- `Button` - Primary action buttons with variants
- `Card` - Container for content sections
- `Input` - Form input fields
- `Dialog` - Modal dialogs and overlays
- `Select` - Dropdown selection components
- `Badge` - Status indicators and labels

## Component Usage Patterns
- Use `cn()` utility for conditional styling
- Follow shadcn/ui variant patterns (default, secondary, destructive, etc.)
- Maintain consistent spacing using Tailwind classes
- Use proper semantic HTML elements

## Theming
- Components support light/dark themes via CSS custom properties
- Theme toggle available via [src/components/theme-toggle.tsx](mdc:src/components/theme-toggle.tsx)
- Colors defined in [tailwind.config.ts](mdc:tailwind.config.ts)

## Icons
- Use Lucide React icons consistently
- Import specific icons: `import { IconName } from "lucide-react"`
- Maintain consistent icon sizes (h-4 w-4, h-6 w-6, etc.)

## Layout Patterns
- Use container classes for responsive layouts
- Implement proper grid systems for card layouts
- Maintain consistent padding and margins
- Use flexbox for component alignment

## Form Components
- Implement proper form validation
- Use controlled components with React state
- Handle form submission with proper event handling
- Provide user feedback for form states